****************************************
***           REQUIREMENTS           ***
****************************************

CS4500 Assignment 4 requires the use a CCIS Linux machine and Python 2.6+

****************************************
***            HOW TO USE            ***
****************************************

In order to run the program on a CCIS Linux machine, please use this format:

FORMAT
    ./cs4500 <input_file> <output_file>
EXAMPLE
    ./cs4500 ~/test_inputs/StackInt.txt ~/test_outputs/output.txt


****************************************
***     IMPORTANT NOTES TO GRADER    ***
***        BUGS AND PROBLEMS         ***
****************************************

This is the second submitted version of CS4500 Assignment 4.
The following problems exist and will be addressed in the next
assignment: 

    - Identifier evaluates to string rather than Scheme expressions
        This is due to ambigious grammar definitions. Will be addressed
        in future assignments.
    - The program will not generate expected results when input_file
        contains multiple signatures.
        NOTE: Multiple signatures were not a requirement for this 
        assignment. However, it was identified as a potential issue.

